## 🔬 Detailed Analysis

### 1. 🌏 Remote DB Latency (ROOT CAUSE)

```
DB_HOST=database-1.cdmaqckkenlv.ap-southeast-2.rds.amazonaws.com
```

Your RDS is in **Sydney (ap-southeast-2)**, but you're developing from **India**. Each DB round-trip adds **150-300ms**. 

**Login flow alone makes 4 sequential DB calls:**
1. `User.findOne({ where: { email } })` — ~200ms
2. `user.update({ last_login_at })` — ~200ms  
3. [resolveEntity(user)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) → S3 signed URL for `profile_pic_url` — ~200ms
4. JWT signing (CPU, fast) — ~5ms

**Total: ~600ms minimum** just for login, without bcrypt.

> [!TIP]
> **Fix:** For development, use a local MySQL instance. For production, ensure your app server (EC2/ECS) is in the **same AWS region** as your RDS (ap-southeast-2).

---

### 2. 🔓 bcrypt Cost (Salt Rounds = 10)

```javascript
// .env
BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS=10

// auth.service.js:44
const isMatch = await bcrypt.compare(password, user.password_hash);
```

`bcrypt.compare` with **10 salt rounds** takes **~200-400ms on average hardware**. This is by design (security), but combined with remote DB latency, it compounds the problem.

> [!TIP]
> **Fix:** Don't reduce salt rounds (security risk). Instead, focus on reducing DB round-trips around the bcrypt call. The bcrypt cost is acceptable — the problem is everything else adding up.

---

### 3. 🗄️ ZERO Database Indexes on Foreign Keys

> [!WARNING]
> **None of your 40 models define ANY explicit indexes.** Sequelize does NOT auto-create indexes on foreign keys (only MySQL InnoDB creates them for declared FK constraints, but Sequelize's `sync` often doesn't create proper FK constraints).

**Critical missing indexes:**

| Table | Column(s) | Used In | Query Pattern |
|-------|-----------|---------|---------------|
| `users` | `email` | Login, Register, Forgot password | `WHERE email = ?` |
| `users` | `role` | notifyRoles, Dashboard | `WHERE role IN (...)` |
| `users` | `client_id` | Job create, Approve, Authorize | `WHERE client_id = ? AND role = 'CLIENT'` |
| `users` | `status` | Auth middleware | Combined with findByPk |
| `job_requests` | `vessel_id` | Jobs list, Client dashboard | `WHERE vessel_id IN (...)` |
| `job_requests` | `job_status` | Dashboard counts, Job filters | `GROUP BY job_status` |
| `job_requests` | `assigned_surveyor_id` | Surveyor dashboard, Survey access | `WHERE assigned_surveyor_id = ?` |
| `job_requests` | `certificate_type_id` | Job list includes | JOIN on CertificateType |
| `job_requests` | `requested_by_user_id` | Job list filters | `WHERE requested_by_user_id = ?` |
| `job_requests` | `created_at` | Recent jobs filter | `WHERE created_at >= ?` |
| `surveys` | `job_id` (UNIQUE) | ✅ Has unique constraint | OK |
| `surveys` | `surveyor_id` | Surveyor dashboard | `WHERE surveyor_id = ?` |
| `surveys` | `survey_status` | Dashboard grouping | `GROUP BY survey_status` |
| `job_status_histories` | `job_id` | Job detail, history | `WHERE job_id = ?` |
| `survey_status_histories` | `survey_id` | Survey detail | `WHERE survey_id = ?` |
| `notifications` | `user_id` | Get notifications | `WHERE user_id = ?` |
| `notifications` | `created_at` | Notification list | `ORDER BY created_at DESC` |
| `gps_tracking` | `job_id` | Survey timeline | `WHERE job_id = ?` |
| `gps_tracking` | `surveyor_id` | GPS stream | `WHERE surveyor_id = ?` |
| `certificates` | `vessel_id` | Cert list, Client dashboard | `WHERE vessel_id IN (...)` |
| `certificates` | `status` | Expiring certs, Dashboard | `WHERE status = 'VALID'` |
| `certificates` | `expiry_date` | Expiring certs | `WHERE expiry_date BETWEEN` |
| `certificates` | `certificate_number` | Verify cert | `WHERE certificate_number = ?` |
| `payments` | `job_id` | Client dashboard | `WHERE job_id IN (...)` |
| `activity_plannings` | `job_id` | Survey submit, checklist | `WHERE job_id = ?` |
| `non_conformities` | `job_id` + `status` | Finalize survey, cert gen | `WHERE job_id = ? AND status NOT IN (...)` |
| `job_documents` | `job_id` | Verify docs | `WHERE job_id = ?` |
| `audit_logs` | `entity_name` + `entity_id` | Audit queries | `WHERE entity_name = ? AND entity_id = ?` |
| `vessels` | `client_id` | Vessel list, Dashboard | `WHERE client_id = ?` |
| `vessels` | `imo_number` | ✅ Has unique constraint | OK |
| `surveyor_profiles` | `user_id` | Eligible surveyors, Dashboard | `WHERE user_id = ?` |
| `surveyor_profiles` | `status` | Eligible surveyors | `WHERE status = 'ACTIVE'` |
| `certificate_required_documents` | `certificate_type_id` | Job create, verify docs | `WHERE certificate_type_id = ?` |
| `notification_preferences` | `user_id` | Notification service | `WHERE user_id = ?` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Without indexes, every `WHERE` clause on these columns does a FULL TABLE SCAN.** As your data grows from 100 to 10,000 rows, these queries will go from 50ms to 5000ms+.

