### 4. ☁️ [resolveEntity](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) — S3 Signed URL on Every Response

```javascript
// fileAccess.service.js:94
export const resolveEntity = async (data, user = null) => {
    // Recursively walks EVERY object/array in the response
    // For each URL key (profile_pic_url, file_url, etc.)
    // Makes an AWS S3 getSignedUrl() call — ~50-100ms each
}
```

**This function is called on virtually EVERY API response:**

| Service | Line | Impact |
|---------|------|--------|
| `auth.service.js:51` | Login — [resolveEntity(user)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | 1 signed URL call for profile_pic |
| `auth.service.js:97` | Register — [resolveEntity(user)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | 1 signed URL call |
| `auth.service.js:131` | Refresh Token — [resolveEntity(user)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | 1 signed URL call |
| `job.service.js:267` | Get Jobs list — [resolveEntity(rows)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | **N signed URL calls** (one per job with attached docs) |
| `job.service.js:322` | Get Job by ID — [resolveEntity(jobPlain)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | Multiple signed URLs (docs, certs, surveys) |
| `survey.service.js:171` | Upload proof — [resolveEntity({url})](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | 1 signed URL |
| `survey.service.js:291` | Submit survey — [resolveEntity(survey)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | 3-5 signed URLs |
| `survey.service.js:418` | Timeline — [resolveEntity(survey)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | Multiple signed URLs |
| `survey.service.js:442` | Survey reports — [resolveEntity(rows)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | N × multiple signed URLs |
| `survey.service.js:458` | Survey details — [resolveEntity(survey)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/fileAccess.service.js#88-126) | Multiple signed URLs |

**For a job list with 10 jobs, each with 2 documents, this generates ~20 S3 signed URL calls** — at ~50ms each with AWS SDK overhead, that's easily **+1 second**.

> [!TIP]
> **Fix Options:**
> 1. **Use CloudFront signed cookies** instead of per-URL signing — authenticate once, access all
> 2. **Cache signed URLs** in-memory with TTL (they're valid for 3600s, cache for 3000s)
> 3. **Lazy URL resolution** — return S3 keys, let frontend call a dedicated `/files/sign` endpoint only when needed
> 4. For `profile_pic_url`: Use CloudFront CDN for public profile pics

