### 5. 🔐 Auth Middleware — DB Query on Every Request

```javascript
// auth.middleware.js:28
const user = await db.User.findByPk(decoded.id);
```

**Every authenticated API call** makes a DB round-trip to fetch the full user object. With remote RDS, that's +200ms on every single request.

> [!TIP]
> **Fix:** Cache the user object in-memory (Map/LRU cache) with a short TTL (60s). The JWT already contains [id](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/vessels/vessel.service.js#7-16), `role`, and `email` — for most APIs, that's enough without hitting the DB.

```javascript
// Proposed fix:
const userCache = new Map();
const USER_CACHE_TTL = 60_000; // 60 seconds

export const authenticate = async (req, res, next) => {
    // ... token extraction and verification ...
    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, env.jwt.accessSecret);
    
    const cached = userCache.get(decoded.id);
    if (cached && Date.now() - cached.ts < USER_CACHE_TTL) {
        req.user = cached.user;
        req.token = token;
        return next();
    }
    
    const user = await db.User.findByPk(decoded.id);
    if (!user || user.status !== 'ACTIVE') { ... }
    
    userCache.set(decoded.id, { user, ts: Date.now() });
    req.user = user;
    req.token = token;
    next();
};
```

