### 6. 🔗 N+1 Query Problems

#### 6a. [sendNotification](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/notification.service.js#11-101) — N+1 per notification

```javascript
// notification.service.js:22
const pref = await NotificationPreference.findOne({ where: { user_id: user.id } });
```
Every [sendNotification](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/notification.service.js#11-101) call makes a **separate DB query** for the user's notification preference. When [notifyRoles(['ADMIN', 'GM', 'TM'], ...)](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/notification.service.js#109-188) is called, it fetches all users with an include, but [sendNotification](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/services/notification.service.js#11-101) (individual) does not.

#### 6b. [validateSurveyorAuthority](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#34-82) — 3 sequential queries

```javascript
// job.service.js:38-55
const profile = await SurveyorProfile.findOne({ where: { user_id: surveyorId } });
const vessel = await Vessel.findByPk(job.vessel_id);           // +1 query
const certType = await CertificateType.findByPk(job.certificate_type_id); // +1 query
```

These could be **one query** with includes, or the vessel/certType could be passed from the caller.

#### 6c. Job workflow functions — repeated `findByPk` + `include: ['Vessel']`

Almost every job workflow function ([verifyJobDocuments](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#426-467), [approveRequest](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#468-491), [assignSurveyor](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#507-534), [authorizeSurvey](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#574-603), [reviewJob](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/jobs/job.service.js#604-626), etc.) does:

```javascript
const job = await requireJob(id);  // findByPk (query 1)
// ... business logic ...
const jobWithVessel = await JobRequest.findByPk(id, { include: ['Vessel'] }); // query 2 (SAME job, with vessel)
```

**The same job is fetched twice** — once without vessel, then again with vessel just for the notification message. This is +200ms per workflow call.

#### 6d. Client Dashboard — Sequential N+1

```javascript
// dashboard.service.js:258-277
const jobs = await JobRequest.findAll({ where: { vessel_id: vesselIds } });  // ALL jobs, no limit!
const certificates = await Certificate.findAll({ where: { vessel_id: vesselIds } }); // ALL certificates!
const payments = await Payment.findAll({ where: { job_id: jobIds } }); // ALL payments!
```

- No pagination on any of these
- Fetches ALL jobs/certificates/payments for all client vessels
- Gets worse as data grows

