### 7. 📊 Dashboard Queries

#### Admin Dashboard — 9 parallel queries (acceptable pattern, but heavy)

```javascript
// dashboard.service.js:20-55
const [...] = await Promise.all([
    User.findAll({ group: ['role'] }),           // COUNT + GROUP
    Client.findAll({ include: [Vessel] }),       // FULL CLIENT + VESSEL JOIN
    Vessel.count(),                              // COUNT
    JobRequest.count(),                          // COUNT
    Certificate.count(),                         // COUNT
    SurveyorProfile.count(),                     // COUNT
    JobRequest.findAll({ group: ['job_status'] }),  // COUNT + GROUP
    Certificate.findAll({ group: ['status'] }),     // COUNT + GROUP
    Survey.findAll({ group: ['survey_status'] }),   // COUNT + GROUP
]);
```

The `Promise.all` is good, but `Client.findAll({ include: [Vessel, FlagAdministration] })` fetches **ALL clients with ALL vessels** — this is an unbounded query.

#### GM/TM Dashboard — calls [getAdminDashboard()](file:///Users/abhinavvishwakarma/work/GIRIK/GIRIK_BACKEND/src/modules/dashboard/dashboard.service.js#8-128) 😱

```javascript
export const getGMDashboard = async () => {
    const admin = await getAdminDashboard();
    return { ...admin, role: 'GM' };
}
```

Every GM/TM dashboard call runs the **full ADMIN dashboard query** — 9 parallel queries.

